# =============================================================================
# Root .gitignore — OpenSkeleton mono-repo
#
# Grouped by ecosystem so it's obvious why each entry exists. Each surface
# (backend / web / android / …) may add its own scoped .gitignore for
# tool-specific noise; this root file covers what's common across the repo plus
# the security-critical blocks that must apply everywhere.
# =============================================================================

# --- Secrets & environment (NEVER commit) -----------------------------------
# Real env files are per-machine / per-environment. Only the committed template
# (.env.example, added by a later ticket) is tracked.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.local

# Credential material — defense-in-depth. This project is keyless (deploys use
# GitHub OIDC), so none of these files should ever exist in the first place.
# Blocking them by pattern means a service-account key, ADC dump, or signing
# cert can't be committed and leaked by accident.
*-key.json
*-credentials.json
service-account*.json
application_default_credentials.json
gha-creds-*.json
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.key
*.keystore
*.jks

# --- Java / Maven / Gradle (backend) ----------------------------------------
target/
build/
*.class
*.jar
*.war
*.ear
hs_err_pid*
replay_pid*
.gradle/
.mvn/timing.properties
# ...but keep the build-tool wrappers: they're committed so a fresh clone can
# build without a pre-installed Maven/Gradle. (Negated because *.jar hid them.)
!.mvn/wrapper/maven-wrapper.jar
!gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar

# --- Node / JavaScript (web, tooling) ---------------------------------------
node_modules/
dist/
coverage/
.next/
.nuxt/
.turbo/
*.tsbuildinfo
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# --- Android (mobile shell) -------------------------------------------------
# The Capacitor-generated native project lives at android/ (OSK-146). It ships
# its own android/.gitignore covering build/, .gradle/, local.properties, the
# copied web assets (app/src/main/assets/public) and other generated files, all
# of which `npx cap sync android` regenerates — so only the source project is
# committed. The entries below are the repo-wide belt-and-braces equivalents.
*.apk
*.aab
*.ap_
*.dex
local.properties
.cxx/
captures/
# ...but DO keep the Gradle wrapper JAR: it's committed so a fresh clone / CI
# runner can build with ./gradlew and no pre-installed Gradle. The root *.jar
# rule (Java section above) otherwise hides it, and the root-anchored negation
# there doesn't reach the nested android/ path — so re-include it explicitly for
# any gradle/wrapper location.
!**/gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar

# --- macOS ------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes

# --- IDEs / editors ---------------------------------------------------------
.idea/
*.iml
.vscode/
*.swp
